Bandits in their sustained invasion of communities in Kaduna State kidnapped 11 persons, injuring one victim during the invasion of Angwar Maji community at Jere town, Kagarko Local Government Area, Kaduna State.
The bandits, said to be in large numbers, invaded the community at about 11.00pm, shooting furiously as they were moving from house to house, kidnapping residents. There was minimal resistance during the operations.
Angwar Maji community was identified to be adjacent to the Abuja-Kaduna highway and Kaduna- Bwari Road, encroaching the Federal Capital Territory.
